<div class="badge"><span class="badge-dot"></span>Industry guide</div>
<h1 class="hero-h">Claude for <em style="color:#00C853;font-style:italic;">real estate brokerages.</em></h1>
<p class="hero-sub">Most real estate AI content focuses on individual agents. The brokerage workflow is different, agent enablement, recruiting, transaction oversight, marketing infrastructure. Claude provides leverage at the brokerage level that compounds across every agent. Here is the framework.</p>
</div></div>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Brokerage-specific workflows</span><h2 class="h2">Where AI helps the brokerage itself</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>1. Agent enablement content.</strong> Listing description templates, social content libraries, buyer guide drafts that every agent can customize.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>2. Recruiting outreach.</strong> Personalized outreach to potential agents from other firms.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>3. Transaction coordinator workflows.</strong> Compliance checklist generation, document review, status updates to all parties.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>4. Broker-of-record reviews.</strong> Faster review of agent files for compliance issues.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>5. Office marketing.</strong> Brokerage-level brand content, market reports, community engagement.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">Compliance considerations</span><h2 class="h2">What brokerages must address</h2>
    <p class="body"><strong>1. Fair Housing.</strong> AI-generated listing descriptions and marketing must comply with Fair Housing requirements. Bias review is essential.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>2. License regulations.</strong> State real estate commissions are creating AI usage guidance. Check yours.</p>
    <p class="body"><strong>3. Broker-of-record liability.</strong> AI does not reduce broker liability for agent activities. Compliance review of AI use is part of the BOR job.</p>
    </div></section>

<section><div class="sec-inner"><span class="lbl">What this means for agents</span><h2 class="h2">Trickle-down impact</h2>
    <p class="body">Agents benefit from the brokerage Claude Projects (templates, scripts, market data) without needing to build their own.</p>
    <p class="body">Brokerage-level AI deployment differentiates the firm in agent recruiting, top agents look for tools the firm provides.</p>
    <p class="body">The brokerage that deploys AI well has higher per-agent productivity, which over time compounds into competitive advantage.</p>
    </div></section>

